[SN]TITLE[SN]
Motorbike pillion passenger badly hurt in Selkirk crash

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A pillion passenger has been seriously hurt in an accident involving an off-road motorbike in the Scottish Borders.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The incident happened about 20:30 on Saturday in the Riverside Road area, close to Victoria Park.
A 28-year-old man, thought to be a pillion passenger, suffered a serious head injury and is being treated in the Western General Hospital in Edinburgh.
The rider left the scene and police said they wanted to speak to him or anyone who witnessed the accident.
Sgt Vincent Fisher said: "This incident has left a young man with serious injuries and we are very keen to trace the rider of the motorcycle.
"If you saw this incident, or the off-road motorcycle around the time of the crash, or have any information that can help us with our inquiries, please get in touch."
